cppcoreguidelines-use-enum-class.description:
Description

Finds unscoped (non-class)
enum
declarations and suggests using
enum
class
instead.

This check implements
Enum.3
from the C++ Core Guidelines.‚Äù

Example:

enum
E
{};
// use "enum class E {};" instead
enum
class
E
{};
// OK
struct
S
{
enum
E
{};
// use "enum class E {};" instead
// OK with option IgnoreUnscopedEnumsInClasses
};
namespace
N
{
enum
E
{};
// use "enum class E {};" instead
}
